

=Definition=

FROM JASEcon:

"Collective Houses are houses, owned or rented by a collective, that are structured by principles of cooperative living, direct democracy and mutual aid. Collective members share expenses and the physical and relational work of living together."
(http://jasecon.wik.is/Consumption%2f%2fUse/Collective_Houses)


